'''Alacrite''' (also known as '''L-605''', '''Cobalt L-605''', '''Haynes 25''', and occasionally '''F90'''<ref name="ContSteelL605">{{cite web |url=http://continentalsteel.com/nickel-alloys/grades/l-605-cobalt-l-605-haynes-25/ |title=Nickel Alloy L-605, Cobalt® L-605, Haynes® 25 |publisher=Continental Steel & Tube Company |accessdate=11 March 2016}}</ref><ref name="PoncinL605_06">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=edtoQUe2VxgC&pg=PA85 |chapter=L605 Precipitates and Their Effects on Stent Applications |title=Medical Device Materials III - Proceedings of the Materials & Processes for Medical Devices Conference |author1=Poncin, P. |author2=Gruez, B. |author3=Missillier, P. |author4=Comte-Gaz, P. |author5=Proft, J.L. |editor1=Venugopalan, R. |editor2=Wu, M. |publisher=ASTM International |year=2006 |pages=85–92 |isbn=9781615031153 |accessdate=11 March 2016}}</ref><ref name="BrunskiMetals09">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=b8uWIVbd1WgC&pg=PA239 |chapter=3.2.9 Metals |title=Biomedical Engineering Desk Reference |author =Brunski, J.B. |editor=Academic Press |publisher=Elsevier |year=2009 |pages=230–247 |isbn=9780123746474 |accessdate=11 March 2016}}</ref>) is a family of [[cobalt]]-based [[alloy]]s. The alloy exhibits useful mechanical properties and is [[Redox|oxidation-]] and [[sulfidation]]-resistant.<ref name="PoncinL605_06" />
One member of the family, XSH Alacrite,<ref name="MeuryDef05">{{cite web|url=http://www.lne.fr/publications/actes_12e_congres_metrologie/definition_alliage_metallique_etalon_masse.pdf |format=PDF |title=Définition d'un nouvel alliage métallique pour la réalisation d'étalons de masse secondaires |author1=Meury, P.A. |author2=Molins, R. |author3=Gosset, A. |work=Actes du 12e congrès international de métrologie |publisher=Laboratoire national de métrologie et d’essais |date=June 2005 |accessdate=11 March 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140308194616/http://www.lne.fr/publications/actes_12e_congres_metrologie/definition_alliage_metallique_etalon_masse.pdf |archivedate=8 March 2014 |df= }}</ref> is described as "a non-magnetic, stainless super-alloy whose high surface hardness enables one to achieve a mirror quality polish."<ref name="INM_MGAArch_12">{{cite web |url=http://ww1.cnam.fr/instituts/inm/english/mga/mga.htm |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120330131514/http://ww1.cnam.fr/instituts/inm/english/mga/mga.htm |title=BNM-INM/CNAM - M.G.A. |publisher=L'Institut National de Métrologie |archivedate=30 March 2012 |accessdate=11 March 2016}}</ref> Originally developed for manufacturing aircraft components,<ref name="JonesHand02">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bVXMBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA34 |chapter=Chapter 3: Contamination of Mass Standards |title=Handbook of Mass Measurement |author1=Jones, F.E. |author2=Schoonover, R.M. |publisher=CRC Press |year=2002 |pages=23–36 |isbn=9781420038453 |accessdate=11 March 2016}}</ref> L-605 has also been used in [[aerospace]] components and [[gas turbine|turbine engines]] as well as [[drug-eluting stents|drug-eluting]] and other kinds of [[stent]]s due to its [[biocompatibility]].<ref name="PoncinL605_06" /> The Institut National de Métrologie in [[France]] has also used the material as a [[kilogram]] mass standard.<ref name="INM_MGAArch_12" /><ref name="JonesHand02" />
==Composition and standardization== L-605 is composed primarily of [[cobalt]] (Co), with a specified mixture of [[chromium]] (Cr), [[tungsten]] (W), [[nickel]] (Ni), [[iron]] (Fe) and [[carbon]] (C), as well as small amounts of [[manganese]] (Mn), [[silicon]] (Si), and [[phosphorus]] (P). The tungsten and nickel improve the alloy's machinability,<ref name="BrunskiMetals09" /> while chromium contributes to its solid-solution strengthening.<ref name="PoncinL605_06" /> The following tolerances must be met to be considered an L-605 alloy:<ref name="ContSteelL605" /><ref name="PoncinL605_06" /><ref name="MeuryDef05" /><ref name="JonesHand02" />
{| | STYLE="vertical-align:top;"| {| class="wikitable" border="1" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" width="100%" |- | style="background-color:white; padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;" colspan="9"|Tolerances for L-605 composition |- ! style="padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|Co ! style="padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|Cr ! style="padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|W ! style="padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|Ni ! style="padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|Fe ! style="padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|C ! style="padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|Mn ! style="padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|Si ! style="padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|P |- | style="background-color:white; padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|Balance | style="background-color:white; padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|19–21 | style="background-color:white; padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|14–16 | style="background-color:white; padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|9–11 | style="background-color:white; padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|< 3 | style="background-color:white; padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|0.05–0.15 | style="background-color:white; padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|1–2 | style="background-color:white; padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|< 1 | style="background-color:white; padding-left:10px; padding-right:10px;"|< 0.4 |- |} |}
When used for [[Implant (medicine)|implantable]] [[medical device]]s, the [[ASTM International|ASTM]] F90-09 and [[International Organization for Standardization|ISO]] 5832-5:2005 specifications dictate how L-605 is manufactured and tested.<ref name="PoncinL605_06" /><ref name="BrunskiMetals09" /><ref name="ASTMF90-09">{{cite web |url=http://www.astm.org/DATABASE.CART/HISTORICAL/F90-09.htm |title=ASTM F90-09: Standard Specification for Wrought Cobalt-20Chromium-15Tungsten-10Nickel Alloy for Surgical Implant Applications (UNS R30605) |work=ASTM.org |publisher=ASTM International |accessdate=11 March 2016}}</ref><ref name="ISO 5832">{{cite web |url=http://www.iso.org/iso/iso_catalogue/catalogue_tc/catalogue_detail.htm?csnumber=35169 |title=ISO 5832-5:2005: Implants for surgery -- Metallic materials -- Part 5: Wrought cobalt-chromium-tungsten-nickel alloy |work=ISO.org |publisher=International Organization for Standardization |date=11 March 2016}}</ref>
