'''John Geoffrey "Geoff" Mosley''' (born 14 September 1931) was Executive Director of the [[Australian Conservation Foundation]] from 1973 to 1986 and has had a lifelong interest in preserving wilderness. He has since been regularly elected from [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] to the Council of the Australian Conservation Foundation as the only candidate In Victoria to receive a quota of first preference votes.

His contributions were acknowledged in 2005 when he was made a Member of the [[Order of Australia]] in the Queen's Birthday Honours.<ref>Williams, Christine (2006). ''Green power: Environmentalists who have changed the face of Australia'', Lothian Books, pp. 111-119.</ref> In June, 2008 he was named as the Individual Award winner in the Australia World Environment Day 2008 Awards. In 2008, he also became the Australian Director of the Centre for the Advancement of the Steady State Economy.<ref>http://steadystate.org/meet/our-staff/</ref>

