{{Expand French|Parc national de Kosterhavet|fa=yes|topic=geo|date=December 2011}} {{Infobox protected area | name = Kosterhavet National Park | alt_name = Kosterhavets nationalpark | iucn_category = II | photo = Nordkoster Klapperstensvallar.jpg | photo_width = | photo_caption = | location = [[Bohuslän]], [[Sweden]] | nearest_city = [[Strömstad]] | coords = {{coord|58|50|N|11|01|E|region:SE_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | area = {{convert|388.78|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}<ref name="Kosterhavet">{{cite web| title=Kosterhavet National Park| url=http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Menu/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Kosterhavet-National-Park/| publisher=[[Environmental Protection Agency (Sweden)|Naturvårdsverket]]| accessdate=2009-11-05| deadurl=yes| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090923175443/http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Menu/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Kosterhavet-National-Park| archivedate=2009-09-23| df=}}</ref> | established = 2009 | visitation_num =90,000 | visitation_year = | governing_body = [[Environmental Protection Agency (Sweden)|Environmental Protection Agency]] | url = [http://www.lansstyrelsen.se/vastragotaland/Projektwebbar/Kosterhavet/Information_in_English Official website] }}
'''Kosterhavet National Park''' is the first [[List of national parks of Sweden|national]] [[marine park]] in Sweden, inaugurated on September 2009.<ref name=koster-en>{{cite web|title=Kosterhavets webbplats|url=http://www.lansstyrelsen.se/vastragotaland/Projektwebbar/Kosterhavet/|publisher=[[Västra Götaland County Administrative Board]]|language=Swedish|trans-title=Website of the Kosterhavet Marine National Park|date=10 September 2009|accessdate=10 September 2009}}</ref> It is part of the [[Skagerrak]] sea and is located in [[Strömstad Municipality|Strömstad]] and [[Tanum Municipality|Tanum]] municipalities in [[Bohuslän]], [[Västra Götaland County]], [[Sweden]].<ref name="naturvårdsverket">{{cite web|url= http://www.naturvardsverket.se/sv/Arbete-med-naturvard/Satsning-pa-havsmiljo/Skydd-av-marina-omraden/Kosterhavet-planeras-bli-Sveriges-forsta-marina-nationalpark/|title= Kosterhavet planeras bli Sveriges första marina nationalpark|publisher= [[Environmental Protection Agency (Sweden)|Naturvårdsverket]]|language= Swedish|accessdate= 2009-06-26|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090330195818/http://www.naturvardsverket.se/sv/Arbete-med-naturvard/Satsning-pa-havsmiljo/Skydd-av-marina-omraden/Kosterhavet-planeras-bli-Sveriges-forsta-marina-nationalpark/|archivedate= 2009-03-30|df= }}</ref><ref name=svd>{{cite news|url=http://www.svd.se/nyheter/inrikes/artikel_2618793.svd|title=Sveriges första marina nationalpark|date=19 March 2009|publisher=[[Svenska Dagbladet]]|language=Swedish|trans-title=Sweden's first marine national park|accessdate=26 June 2009}}</ref> It consists of the sea and shores around the [[Koster Islands]], excluding everything else on the islands. In the north, it borders the [[Norway|Norwegian]] marine park of [[Ytre Hvaler National Park|Ytre Hvaler]].
Kosterhavet National Park is home to Sweden's largest seal colony.<ref>Proctor, James (2014). ''West Sweden''. Bradt Travel Guides. Page 51. {{ISBN|9781841625591}}.</ref>
== Nature == [[File:Kosterhavet National Park logo.svg|thumb|left|Kosterhavet's logo]] {{Swedish National Parks}} The environment in the park is unique to Swedish waters. Over 6,000 marine species have been identified, about 200 of them can not to be found elsewhere in Sweden. The Kosterfjord ({{lang-en|Koster Fjord}})<ref>Alander, Harald. 1942. ''Sponges from the Swedish West-Coast and Adjacent Waters''. Göteborg: Henrik Struves boktryckeri, p. 8.</ref><ref>Rice, James (ed.). 2010. ''Great Escapes: 500 Unforgettable Travel Experiences''. London: Rough Guides, p. 104.</ref> is {{convert|200|m|ft|abbr=on}} deep with relatively low temperature – {{convert|5|to|7|°C|°F|0|lk=on}} – and high [[salinity]] (about 35%). [[Brachiopod]], [[sponge]] and [[Lophelia|coral]] larvae are brought in by currents from the Atlantic. Rare seabirds, such as [[Arctic tern]]s and [[skua]]s, along with a large population of [[harbor seal]]s have their habitat here. [[Plaice]], [[cod]] and [[brown trout|sea trout]] breed in the more shallow waters closer to the shore.<ref name="folder">{{cite web|url =http://www.lansstyrelsen.se/NR/rdonlyres/FA3F8AF3-8BEE-4744-8DEF-AE5576CE0E00/149485/nationalparksfoldernENV5lagupplost.pdf|title =Kosterhavet|publisher =[[Environmental Protection Agency (Sweden)|Naturvårdsverket]]|accessdate =10 September 2009}}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref name="poster">{{cite web|url=http://www.lansstyrelsen.se/NR/rdonlyres/3E574BDB-AFF8-4ED7-8740-D296E73E692F/81013/KosterhavetNP_Murcia.pdf|title=Kosterhavet|author=Bengt Frizell (ed)|publisher=[[Västra Götaland County Administrative Board]]|accessdate=10 September 2009}}</ref>
Professional fishing is allowed although special regulations apply. The waters of the park is significant for the fishing of ''[[Pandalus borealis|northern prawn]]'' and [[Nephrops norvegicus|Norwegian lobster]]. Fishing is not subject to environmental protection, and are instead regulated by fishery laws and an agreement from 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sottochsalt.fiskeriverket.se/Article.asp?ArticleId=141|title=Ansvarsfullt yrkesfiske i marin nationalpark|publisher=[[National Board of Fisheries (Sweden)|Swedish Board of Fisheries]]|language=Swedish|trans-title=Responsible fishery in marine national park|accessdate=10 September 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100117083601/http://sottochsalt.fiskeriverket.se/Article.asp?ArticleId=141|archive-date=2010-01-17|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
