'''Spindle oils''' are a type of low-[[viscosity]] [[mineral oil]] marketed for use in [[lubrication]] of high-speed machine [[spindle (tool)|spindle]]s.<ref name="BP" /> Spindle oil is free from gumming properties.<ref>Emmanuel F. Niño, Industrial lubrication, {{ISBN|978-971-23-2178-8}}, p. 52</ref>
Since the viscosity is so low that the oil runs off the surface of the spindle during shut-down periods, the spindle oil may be doped with additives that prevent rusting. Since the spindle oil often is used in textile factories, it is also important that it doesn't stain the textiles.<ref>V. Stepina, Lubricants and special fuels, Elesevier Scientific Publishing, {{ISBN|0-444-98674-X}}, p. 527</ref>

