'''''Symbiosis''''' was a [[70 mm film]]<ref>{{cite book|last1=Pedersen|first1=R. A.|title=The Epcot Explorer's Encyclopdia|date=2012|publisher=Epcyclopedia|location=United States|isbn=1456589660|page=168}}</ref> shown from October 1982 to January 1995 in the Harvest Theater at [[The Land (Disney)|The Land]] pavilion at [[Epcot]] at the [[Walt Disney World Resort]] in [[Lake Buena Vista, Florida]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Smith|first1=Dave|title=Disney A to Z Online Edition - Symbiosis (film)|url=https://d23.com/a-to-z/symbiosis-film/|website=D23|publisher=The Walt Disney Company|accessdate=29 October 2015}}</ref> It was directed by Paul Gerber and narrated by veteran voice-actor [[Philip L. Clarke]].
The movie focused on the balance between technological expansion and the [[Environmental protection|protection of the environment]]. The film showed environmental damage caused by humans and what is being done to fix the damage created.
It closed on January 1, 1995 and was replaced by ''[[Circle of Life: An Environmental Fable]]''. The new film featured some re-edited footage from ''Symbiosis''.
The film has since been shown at film festivals specialising in the 70&nbsp;mm film format; at the [[National Media Museum]] in 1998, and in [[Karlsruhe]], [[Germany]] in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|title = "Symbiosis" Cast & Credits|url = http://www.in70mm.com/news/2012/gerber/symbiosis/index.htm|website = www.in70mm.com|accessdate = 2015-11-03}}</ref>
==Details== * Grand Opening: October 1, 1982 * Director: Paul Gerber * Producer: Sascha Schneider * Assistant Director: [[Paul Lawrence]] * Director of Photography: Eric Saarinen * Camera: [[Marc Wolff]] * Narrator: [[Philip L. Clarke]]
